## Notes

- **MapStruct Behavior:** MapStruct automatically maps all fields including ID. If DTO has ID, entity will have ID.
- **Hibernate Behavior:** If entity has ID set, Hibernate uses INSERT with explicit ID. If ID is null, Hibernate uses sequence generator.
- **Defense in Depth:** Controller check + Service clearing + AOP aspect provides three layers of protection.
- **Performance:** ID clearing has negligible performance impact (simple null check).

## Checklist for New Entity Services

When creating a new entity service with `save()` method:

- [ ] Add ID null check before repository.save()
- [ ] Clear ID if present: `entity.setId(null)`
- [ ] Add warning log when ID is cleared
- [ ] Verify controller checks for ID in create endpoint
- [ ] Test with DTO that has ID set
- [ ] Test with DTO that has null ID
- [ ] Verify sequence generator is used (check logs)
